 while the other inmates of the house, were holding their festive meetings in the adjoining prayer hall. For the visit paid to her & the prayer offered up by her bed side,
						she expressed her thanks in a very cordial & lively manner. Little did the Minister think, that on his return from Crook, whither duty called him away for several days, he
						should no longer be permitted to see her among the living.
